title: Frieze, 1905–15
description: Alternating foliate medallions connected by floral swags. Bottom band of stripes and top band of stripes, beading, egg and dart, and bead and reel patterns. Ground shades from tan to light teal (bottom to top) and is covered with groups of circles connected by vining. Printed in burgundy, tans, beige, teal, brown-green and metallic gold.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-389.
